# {{ project_name }} Infrastructure

Generated by darth-infra as editable CloudFormation templates.

## Layout

- `darth-infra.toml`: source-of-truth project config.
- `templates/generated/root.yaml`: regenerated root stack from TOML.
- `templates/generated/services/*.yaml`: regenerated per-service ECS templates.
- `templates/custom/overrides.yaml`: user-owned stack (never overwritten).

If `[cloudfront].enabled = true`, the root stack also provisions an ALB-backed CloudFront distribution
with uncached default behavior and explicit cached path behaviors from config.
Set `[cloudfront].custom_domain` and `[cloudfront].certificate_arn` to attach an alternate domain.
CloudFront certificates must be in `us-east-1`, and custom domains must be mapped in external DNS.
If `[cloudfront].origin_https_only = true`, the ALB origin must expose HTTPS (`443`).

## Deploy

```bash
# Create + execute a change set
darth-infra deploy --env prod

# Create change set only (no execute)
darth-infra deploy --env prod --no-execute
```

## Destroy

```bash
darth-infra destroy --env dev
```

## Editing

Generated templates under `templates/generated/` are overwritten on `init` and `deploy`.
Put manual CloudFormation changes in `templates/custom/overrides.yaml`; that file is preserved.
